This ioncube decoder is called ironcube, but it decodes ioncube files.  If you read the source code, it even says ioncube in MANY places.  Also, how can this be a fake decoder if they even give you the source code itself?  People, this is legit in the sense that you can even tweak it to your liking.  Its open source apparently.  That being said, there is some kind of error with the zlib tool.ocx.  The original file needed to be registered, but when I used regsvr32 it said it wouldn't work.  I got an updated copy of zlib tool and it registers, but it isn't working well so far.  It fails when it reaches that tool.  So, even a minor revision being used as a replacement doesn't work the same.  I'm not sure why yet, but I'm working on it.
